🧠 Example: Solve a problem with no math symbols at all

Problem

You have a balance scale. One side is heavier.
Find which side is heavier.

⸻

🚫 No numbers

🚫 No algebra

🚫 No geometry

⸻

🔁 Pure relational / procedural solution

You don’t compute anything. You just interact:
	1.	Look at the scale
	2.	Observe which side goes down
	3.	Declare: “that side is heavier”

Done.

⸻

What just happened?

You solved the problem using:
	•	comparison
	•	observation
	•	state transition

No numbers. No equations.

⸻

🧩 Slightly harder problem

You have 3 sealed boxes.
One contains gold. You can open only one.
Each box has a statement on it. Only one statement is true.
Find the gold.

⸻

🧠 Solve using pure logic (no algebra)

Label boxes mentally: A, B, C

Statements:
	•	A: “Gold is in B”
	•	B: “Gold is not in this box”
	•	C: “Gold is in this box”

⸻

🔁 Reasoning (no math symbols)

Assume A is true:
→ Gold is in B
→ Then B says “not in B” (false)
→ C says “in C” (false)
✔ Only one true → valid

⸻

So gold is in B.

⸻

What did we use?
	•	Consistency checking
	•	Assumption → consequence → contradiction
	•	That’s basically logic instead of algebra

⸻

